如果我签了法案  你这书怎么写
no idea if it will end up being relevant if I end up...

520
00:27:22,590 --> 00:27:24,140
还有什么要紧
signing this bill.

521
00:27:24,570 --> 00:27:25,460
你打算签吗
Are you going to?

522
00:27:27,960 --> 00:27:29,360
我还不知道
I don't know yet.

523
00:27:30,230 --> 00:27:31,280
当然  就算我签了法案
If I do, of course,

524
00:27:31,280 --> 00:27:35,300
你的书用不着了  我还是会付全额稿酬的
I'll pay you in full if the book becomes unnecessary.

525
00:27:36,600 --> 00:27:38,170
我写这书不是为了钱
I'm not doing this for the paycheck.

526
00:27:42,600 --> 00:27:43,570
你有什么看法
What do you think?

527
00:27:45,140 --> 00:27:46,160
我该不该签
Should I sign it?

528
00:27:46,280 --> 00:27:47,550
这牵涉到我的利益
Well, I have skin in the game.

529
00:27:48,430 --> 00:27:50,270
所以出于私心  我希望你别签
So the selfish part of me says no.

530
00:27:53,230 --> 00:27:53,990
不过
But...

531
00:27:56,030 --> 00:27:56,900
老实说
honestly?

532
00:27:58,180 --> 00:28:00,230
没有哪本书值得让人送命
No book is worth people losing their lives.

533
00:28:00,230 --> 00:28:02,170
话是没错  但这不只关系到这本书
Yes, but it's not just about the book.

534
00:28:03,620 --> 00:28:05,560
也是为了让人们重回工作岗位
It's about putting people back to work.

535
00:28:05,950 --> 00:28:07,600
如果人都死了  还怎么工作呢
People can't work if they're dead.

536
00:28:11,600 --> 00:28:14,970
我最近一段时间内
Well, I'm gonna obviously be very occupied

537
00:28:14,970 --> 00:28:17,340
都会为这个飓风忙里忙外
by this hurricane for the foreseeable future.

538
00:28:17,930 --> 00:28:19,310
再让我考虑考虑吧
Let me think on this for...

539
00:28:23,630 --> 00:28:25,080
你最好别坑他
You'd better not fuck him over.

540
00:28:25,900 --> 00:28:27,800
-什么  -你写的东西
- Excuse me? - With what you're writing.

541
00:28:28,850 --> 00:28:29,810
我也没这个打算
I don't intend to.

542
00:28:30,220 --> 00:28:32,550
-你在书里说他傻  -你偷听
- The part about being foolish? - You eavesdropping?

543
00:28:32,590 --> 00:28:34,800
-他不傻  -我也没说他傻
- He's not foolish. - That wasn't my point.

544
00:28:34,800 --> 00:28:36,730
我不会为个傻子挡子弹
I wouldn't take a bullet for a man who was.

545
00:28:39,780 --> 00:28:40,990
走吧  你的车已经候着了
Let's go, your car's waiting.

546
00:28:44,330 --> 00:28:45,290
从明天起
As of tomorrow,

547
00:28:45,290 --> 00:28:48,730
夏普议员女士和我将暂停竞选活动
Congresswoman Sharp and I are suspending our campaigns.

548
00:28:49,170 --> 00:28:52,000
我们将赶赴受飓风费斯影响的地区
We will be traveling to areas affected by Hurricane Faith,

549
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:53,610
整个竞选团队也将随行
along with our campaign staff,

550
00:28:54,050 --> 00:28:57,580
以便为灾区贡献我们最大的力量
in order to volunteer in whatever capacity is most helpful.

551
00:28:58,320 --> 00:29:00,430
我们也将暂停接受捐款
We're also suspending any donations,

552
00:29:00,430 --> 00:29:03,360
同时呼吁我们的支持者向红十字会
and urge our supporters to donate to the Red Cross

553
00:29:03,570 --> 00:29:05,500
和其他飓风援助机构捐款
and other hurricane relief agencies.

554
00:29:05,730 --> 00:29:09,730
大灾当前  理应暂停政治活动
In times of suffering, it's important to suspend politics

555
00:29:09,990 --> 00:29:11,920
做对国家有益之事
and do what's best for the country.

556
00:29:12,930 --> 00:29:14,840
我们期待在飓风过去
We look forward to resuming our campaigns

557
00:29:14,840 --> 00:29:16,160
东海岸人民安全之后
when the storm has cleared

558
00:29:16,430 --> 00:29:18,280
重启竞选活动
and the people of the east coast are safe.

559
00:29:19,190 --> 00:29:21,090
以上是民主党总统竞选候选人...
That was democratic precedencial candidate...

560
00:29:21,920 --> 00:29:22,740
弗莱迪
Freddy?

561
00:29:26,530 --> 00:29:28,470
总统想见你  海耶斯先生
The President would like to see you, Mr. Hayes.

562
00:29:29,770 --> 00:29:32,090
我还有两小时才能下班
I still got two hours left on my shift.

563
00:29:32,090 --> 00:29:33,820
没关系  弗莱迪  你可以走了
It's fine, Freddy. You can go.

564
00:29:35,240 --> 00:29:37,300
我能带上我孙子吗
Do you mind if I bring my grandson?

565
00:29:38,140 --> 00:29:40,340
因为飓风  日托所关了
Daycare got shut down 'cause of the storm.

566
00:29:41,350 --> 00:29:43,150
当然可以  有车等着我们
Of course. We got a car waiting.

567
00:29:44,850 --> 00:29:45,970
走吧  杜肖恩
Come on, DeShawn.

568
00:29:49,460 --> 00:29:51,410
我们去见总统
We going to see the president.

569
00:29:56,030 --> 00:29:56,950
弗莱迪
Freddy.

570
00:30:00,820 --> 00:30:03,090
-很高兴见到你  弗兰克  -谢谢你能来
- It's good to see you, Frank. - Thank you for coming.

571
00:30:03,380 --> 00:30:06,820
这就是杜肖恩吧  你好吗  先生
And this must be DeShawn. How are you, sir?

572
00:30:07,180 --> 00:30:09,310
握手真是坚定有力
That is a firm handshake you have.

573
00:30:10,370 --> 00:30:12,470
你想去那张桌子后面坐坐吗
Well, you want to go over and sit at the desk?

574
00:30:13,630 --> 00:30:14,460
去吧
Go ahead.

575
00:30:24,430 --> 00:30:26,170
有时候我也那么干
Yeah, I do that too, sometimes.

576
00:30:28,100 --> 00:30:30,660
那桌子有一天或许会是你的
That desk might be yours one day.

577
00:30:31,550 --> 00:30:33,280
你想当总统吗
Would you like to be the president?

578
00:30:34,890 --> 00:30:35,570
想
Yeah.

579
00:30:35,680 --> 00:30:39,380
要当总统  你得在学校取得好成绩
Well, to be president, you have to get good grades in school.

580
00:30:39,380 --> 00:30:41,660
我看你带了作业来
Now, I see you brought some of your schoolwork with you.

581
00:30:41,660 --> 00:30:44,040
我那边有个办公室
I have an office just around the corner in here,

582
00:30:44,040 --> 00:30:45,980
你或许愿意去那里做作业
maybe you'd like to go do your work in there.

583
00:30:45,980 --> 00:30:49,620
如果你想玩  我们还有游戏机
Or we also have a PlayStation if you'd rather play that.

584
00:30:50,680 --> 00:30:52,790
-你有什么游戏  -很多呢
- What games you got? - Oh, we have plenty of games.

585
00:30:52,790 --> 00:30:53,960
密查姆会带你去
Meechum will show you.

586
00:31:03,560 --> 00:31:04,680
给你拿点什么喝
What can I get for you?

587
00:31:04,710 --> 00:31:06,390
咖啡  苏打水  还是啤酒
Coffee, a soda, a beer?

588
00:31:06,390 --> 00:31:08,520
-不用了  谢谢  -请坐
- No, I'm good, thank you. - Please sit down.

589
00:31:13,540 --> 00:31:16,360
-你注册了《美就法》  -是的
- You signed up for America Works. - I did.

590
00:31:16,510 --> 00:31:19,610
我有四万个你这样的案例
I've got 40,000 case studies just like yours.

591
00:31:20,590 --> 00:31:22,250
我桌上还有一份法案
And I also have a bill on my desk

592
00:31:22,250 --> 00:31:24,820
会斩断支持这四万人的资金
that's gonna cut the funding for all 40,000.

593
00:31:24,820 --> 00:31:26,750
知道  我看新闻了
Yeah, I been following on the news.

594
00:31:27,380 --> 00:31:28,460
我会签了它
I'm gonna sign it.

595
00:31:28,700 --> 00:31:31,090
这场飓风危及太多生命了
There's too many lives at stake with this storm.

596
00:31:31,390 --> 00:31:33,020
听起来那是正确的做法
Sounds like the right thing to do.

597
00:31:33,720 --> 00:31:35,200
弗莱迪  你该有份工作
Freddy, you deserve a job,

598
00:31:35,200 --> 00:31:37,450
而国会在强迫我剥夺它
and Congress is forcing me to take it away.

599
00:31:37,850 --> 00:31:39,550
我跟我们的运营主管谈过
I've spoken to our head of operations,

600
00:31:39,550 --> 00:31:41,960
如果你愿意  这里有份给你的工作
and if you want it, there's a job for you here.

601
00:31:41,960 --> 00:31:44,250
-这不是施舍你  但...  -薪水多少
- Now, it's not charity, but-- - What's the pay?

602
00:31:45,190 --> 00:31:46,790
我不知道具体数字
Well, I don't know the exact figures,

603
00:31:46,800 --> 00:31:49,410
但我猜大概每月三千美金左右吧
but I figure somewhere around three grand a month.

604
00:31:49,410 --> 00:31:51,260
-我知道不多  但...  -医保有吗
- I know that's not great, but I-- - Healthcare?

605
00:31:52,700 --> 00:31:53,910
当然有  包括那个
Well, yes, of course. That's included.

606
00:31:53,910 --> 00:31:56,600
-杜肖恩能用吗  -当然  所有家属都能用
- For DeShawn, too? - That's right. All dependents.

607
00:31:57,200 --> 00:31:59,300
-什么工作  -厨房
- What's the job? - The kitchen.

608
00:31:59,910 --> 00:32:01,920
帮厨师们备菜
Helping prep food for the chefs.

609
00:32:02,340 --> 00:32:05,620
只要薪水在每月两千八以上
Well, as long as it's, you know, above 2,800 a month.

610
00:32:05,620 --> 00:32:06,890
我需要那么多来付房租
That's what I need to make my rent

611
00:32:06,890 --> 00:32:09,070
并保证杜肖恩什么都不缺
and make sure DeShawn has everything he needs.

612
00:32:09,070 --> 00:32:11,350
我马上帮你联系主厨
I'll put you in touch with the head chef right away.

613
00:32:11,820 --> 00:32:14,850
不知道...你还有其他工作吗
I was wondering... if you had anything else?

614
00:32:15,420 --> 00:32:18,160
-除了厨房的  -我以为...
- Besides the kitchen. - Well, I just assumed that--

615
00:32:18,160 --> 00:32:20,280
我一辈子都在厨房里工作
I've been working in kitchens my whole life.

616
00:32:20,550 --> 00:32:23,910
我虽开过肋排馆不代表我喜欢厨房
Just 'cause I owned a rib joint don't mean I like working in 'em.

617
00:32:23,960 --> 00:32:25,340
那你想做什么
Well, what would you rather do?

618
00:32:26,930 --> 00:32:28,840
我看你们雇了园丁
You got groundskeepers out there.

619
00:32:29,430 --> 00:32:32,270
车开进来时我看到他们在给树剪枝
I noticed 'em choppin' branches when we were driving in,

620
00:32:32,270 --> 00:32:33,210
为飓风做准备
for the hurricane.

621
00:32:34,180 --> 00:32:35,320
你喜欢那个
You'd prefer that?

622
00:32:35,830 --> 00:32:37,510
一直都想在室外工作
Always wanted to work outside.

623
00:32:38,220 --> 00:32:40,660
这肯定可以安排
Well, I'm sure that something can be arranged.

624
00:32:43,760 --> 00:32:45,070
我也想哪天能当总统
I want to be president one day.

625
00:32:45,310 --> 00:32:48,030
-那永远不可能  -但他说我可以
- Well, that's never gonna happen. - But he said I could be.

626
00:32:48,680 --> 00:32:51,430
听着  孩子  他骗你的
Listen up, boy. He lied to you.

627
00:32:51,550 --> 00:32:53,810
事实是  你永远不可能当上总统
The truth is, you ain't never gonna be president.

628
00:32:54,250 --> 00:32:58,160
就像你海报里的那些篮球运动员
It's just like them basketball players you got posters of.

629
00:32:58,160 --> 00:33:01,410
他们说你能做成任何事  当超级巨星
They say you can do anything, be a superstar, too.

630
00:33:01,640 --> 00:33:04,740
但他们基因好  能长两米多  如果不是呢
But they were born to be seven feet tall and if they wasn't,

631
00:33:04,740 --> 00:33:06,100
你说说他们还能有什么
tell me what would they have?

632
00:33:06,620 --> 00:33:07,560
一无所有
Nothing.

633
00:33:07,800 --> 00:33:10,270
他们中有一半连字都不识
Half of them can't even read a damn book.

634
00:33:10,640 --> 00:33:13,190
孩子  这里不是你我能待的地方
No, boy, this place ain't for you and me.

635
00:33:13,430 --> 00:33:17,930
有梦想是好事  别妄想就行
It's good to have dreams, just so long as they're not fantasies.

636
00:33:17,930 --> 00:33:20,920
如果你被这套糊弄了  就只能怪自己了
You let anybody sell you that shit, it's your own damn fault.

637
00:33:20,920 --> 00:33:22,820
-听见了吗  -听见了  爷爷
- You hear me? - Yeah, I hear you, Pop.

638
00:33:41,210 --> 00:33:42,550
我立即送去国会
I'll get it to the House right away.

639
00:33:43,480 --> 00:33:45,270
-能通知媒体吗  -可以
- Green light on the release? - Yes.

640
00:33:53,540 --> 00:33:55,280
我不记得给过你我的号码
I don't remember giving you my phone number.

641
00:33:55,280 --> 00:33:57,260
你是没给  你的出版商给了
You didn't. Your publisher did.

642
00:33:57,760 --> 00:33:59,010
他想让我写本书
He wants me to write a book.

643
00:33:59,920 --> 00:34:01,270
你没出过书我倒觉得意外
I'm surprised you never have.

644
00:34:02,040 --> 00:34:04,920
我敢说不管你写什么都会卖得有我十倍好
I'm sure any book you wrote would do ten times what mine do.

645
00:34:05,870 --> 00:34:07,420
肯定赶不上《天蝎》
Not as much as Scorpio.

646
00:34:10,010 --> 00:34:11,410
比我之后的作品好
As any I've written since.

647
00:34:12,220 --> 00:34:13,370
我上大学时看的
I read it in college.

648
00:34:14,070 --> 00:34:15,280
改变你人生了吗
Did it change your life?

649
00:34:16,620 --> 00:34:18,320
你是不是整天听人说这个
That's what you hear all day long, isn't it?

650
00:34:18,320 --> 00:34:21,500
那得有人能在大街上认出我  不过没有
If I still got recognized on the street, which I don't.

651
00:34:21,500 --> 00:34:22,700
主要是在签售会上
Mostly at book signings,

652
00:34:22,710 --> 00:34:25,400
如果你写书  我建议你别开签售会
which I don't recommend if you write your book.

653
00:34:25,480 --> 00:34:27,350
我请你来不是讨论我的书的
I didn't ask you here to discuss my book.

654
00:34:27,720 --> 00:34:29,400
-不是吗  -我想谈谈你的书
- No? - I want to discuss yours.

655
00:34:31,580 --> 00:34:33,870
我正在写一篇报道  如果没有白宫的评论
I'm working on a piece, and it won't go to print

656
00:34:33,870 --> 00:34:36,000
我就没法刊登出去
unless I get a comment from the White House.

657
00:34:36,780 --> 00:34:37,710
我不为白宫干活
I'm not a part of the White House.

658
00:34:37,710 --> 00:34:38,670
不非得是原话
Doesn't even have to be a quote,

659
00:34:38,670 --> 00:34:42,120
只要让我能改述一下就行  比如说
just something... that I can paraphrase, like,

660
00:34:42,400 --> 00:34:45,020
"据与政府联系紧密  不愿透露姓名人士称"
"According to someone close to the administration..."

661
00:34:45,270 --> 00:34:46,690
不非得公开
Doesn't have to be on the record.

662
00:34:46,700 --> 00:34:48,250
我不会就我的书发表评论的
I'm not commenting on the book.

663
00:34:48,500 --> 00:34:50,460
汤姆  你能知道别人无从得知的事
Tom, you got access no one else has.

664
00:34:50,460 --> 00:34:52,430
有原因的  因为他知道我管得住嘴
For a reason. 'Cause he knows I won't talk.

665
00:34:52,700 --> 00:34:54,020
尤其是对你
Especially to you.

666
00:34:57,300 --> 00:34:58,500
我总可以请你喝一杯吧
Well, can I buy you a drink?

667
00:34:59,300 --> 00:35:00,640
灌醉我可不好使
Getting me drunk won't work.

668
00:35:00,750 --> 00:35:02,780
你大老远来见我  我欠你一杯酒
You came out to meet me here. I owe you one.

669
00:35:05,190 --> 00:35:06,520
不如我请你喝一杯
Why don't I buy you a drink?

670
00:35:08,470 --> 00:35:09,670
多来几杯怎么样
How about we have a few?

671
00:35:11,740 --> 00:35:12,820
多几杯啊
A few.

672
00:35:13,950 --> 00:35:15,060
行啊
I can live with that.

673
00:35:21,770 --> 00:35:24,650
我真遗憾  弗兰西斯  我知道这有多难
I'm so sorry, Francis. I know how hard this is.

674
00:35:24,690 --> 00:35:27,410
我也没办法啊  天气我管不了
It was out of my hands. I can't control the weather.

675
00:35:28,340 --> 00:35:29,250
终究不好受
Still.

676
00:35:31,610 --> 00:35:33,390
最让我不痛快的
What frustrates me more than anything

677
00:35:33,390 --> 00:35:34,870
就是我们本来已经开始扭转局面了
is we were starting to turn the ship.

678
00:35:34,870 --> 00:35:37,430
国会开始支持我了  再过几个月
I was getting support in Congress. A few more months...

679
00:35:37,590 --> 00:35:39,480
领导层就将别无选择
